\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Your name please Mrs Webster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Elsie Margaret.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 33 Lyttleton Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Liverpool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 17.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And you are }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12989175 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What was your year of marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you know I can't truthfully say - I think it was 1924. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 1895. I know that all right. Don't have to stop and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 35 Lucerne Street - locally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 That's Liverpool 15?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 17.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes, yes, twelve years. Yes, twelve years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 We went over to my grandmother's house 'cos that was a bit bigger and that was number 38 Lucerne Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 So it was in the same street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How long did you live there - up 'til 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh I should - I should think about twenty years. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You say you moved from this house in Lucerne street to the other one because it was a bigger house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes - it had an extra room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It was your grandmother's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It as my grandmother - she died and my father wanted to go to the old home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Sort of ending up where he started off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 That's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 I had - two brothers and three sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What sort of spacing were they - where were you in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
I was the eldest - and in twelve months another sister came. In eighteen months another came. Another eighteen months a sister came and then two years another sister came. And then I quite - I can't quite but I think it'd be about four or five yea
rs when the last brother came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 So they were more or less evenly spaced out except for the last one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 He was a surprise for mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh - she wanted a lovely baby boy. She got - he was a lovely baby boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well round about twenty-eight. Yes. And my mother - both the same age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 He - he - he was born in Lark Lane. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And what was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 He was a grocer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did he have his own shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 He was a manager. Of White Pegrams. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 One of the big chain stores?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, it was just a private one in them days. Yes, Pegrams was just private in them days. They had about twelve shops I think and - it wa}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15475069\charrsid804585 s just tea and - they didn't sel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
l all the stores they've got now in later years. Tea and coffee was their biggest - and he had to serve his time, his mother had to pay them to be - yes, she had to pay him to go and learn to be a grocer. Yes, and he walked 
from Lark Lane right down to the town because he couldn't afford to give him - for - she gave him a penny to come home at night time 'cos he'd be tired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you remember how much she paid for him to be trained?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, I - I never heard that - no, I never heard that Mrs Hoskinson. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did he have another job before or after he became a grocer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 He - he - with the same firm all - all - all his life, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did he do any other causal or part time jobs apart from this work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Until the time of his death was he working or had he retired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Well he - they - they were going to give up the shop he'd been in all those years and he just died of a broken heart. He really felt it. Yes, so much - very, very sad it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Never. That was his one dread. He had little children and he wouldn't - my mother said, many a time she would have liked to have kept him home with a heavy cold. No, he would go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Because he was frightened he might l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15475069\charrsid804585 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 se his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 That was what he was terrified of. 'Cos no money in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 There was nothing spare to fall back on?
