\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 But normally you wouldn't have had cakes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. Only bread and butter and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And Sunday you'd have had the joint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well Sunday was - oh yes, 'cos they were ve
ry cheap Mrs Hoskinson - very cheap, and she'd get a - perhaps a leg of lamb or mutton or piece of beef and - and that lasted of course 'cos I don't think we were very big meat eaters. And she always made a big rice pudding on a Sunday and - I can see it 
in the oven now. Some wanted it and some didn't. And then for tea - I don't think - light cakes. As a great treat we used to have lard cakes on a Sunday 'cos a pe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7287332\charrsid804585 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 son in the street used to make them - they used to come round selling them in a basket and we used to have these lard cakes. Sundays tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 My mother baked all our bread. About three times a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did she make her own jam or bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes. Oh no, she made all - all the jam, no 
bought jam ever came in them days - 'cos fruit was so cheap and sugar was so cheap. Yes. I remember saying - go and ask Auntie Alice has she got any jam jars. Go and ask somebody else have they got any jam jars. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did she make any pickles or wine or medicine for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Never - never wines or anything like that but she used to do a few picled onions 'cos my father used to like them. Yes. But we didn't like them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 They were made specially for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What about medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No homemade but every Friday night when we came home from school we were dosed with licorice powder. And in the summer sh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1982167\charrsid804585 e used to do - treacle and sulf}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 ur. I couldn't bear those.
