\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 This friend of your father's - would he ever come to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. No, he never - yes, my father'd know where to meet him and - he'd go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Would any friends if they called in be offered anything to eat or drink - did they call in casually or would they always be invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Well - I don't remember anybody ever coming to have a real meal with us Mrs Hoskinson No, I don't but I remember me mother making a cup of tea for somebody but never - that's right. She didn't have time to invite people. No. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What do you think - your parents did when they did have a friend in - did they make music or play games or mainly talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well I remember - just a piano
 being played and - and there'd be a fire lit in - in the front room you know and that. We thought that was lovely you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Many people divide society into different social classes or groups - in that time before 1918 did you think of some peopl
e belonging to one and some to another class and could you tell me what the different ones were? Can you put people into social classes at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, I can't Mrs - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What class would you say you belonged to yourself in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you mean middle class? Yes, yes. Yes. Yes. 'Cos we were brought up nicely and - yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What sort of people belonged to the same middle class group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well there was several nice gentlemen lived down there and they were in offices in town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Clerical jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Yes, clerical jobs, yes. And - the - two or three very nice families but there were seafaring and - you know - I suppose they were the sons, I don't know, but they'd bring something home from sea for us children y
ou know when we - this is when we were little. Yes. Very nice. One man bought a lot of oranges once and oh they were lovely. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What sort of people belonged to the other classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well - well there's some very rough people Mrs Hoskinson an
d of course my mother wouldn't let us have anything to do - swearing you know and - rough houses like - they'd have drink and there'd be some rows going on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Would this make them different because they were rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Not exactly - next - this would be in the next street - to where I lived. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Was it mainly because they were rough and used bad language and drinking or was it because they didn't get as much money - would this make them different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It might have been - well it might have bee
n the money and - I don't know really but - I can remember rows in these houses and men shouting and - and the poor woman, I can see them distinctly - I'd only be about that big and this woman ran out. He's going to kill me, he's going to kill me. I was s
cared stiff and ran back to me mother quick. Yes. Oh yes, yes. Remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Can you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music - do you know the expression? If there was somebody that the general population disapproved of in a street and their behaviour was very bad?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes - people were put out of their houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Can you remember people going outside and making a noise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes. Oh yes. they - we used to come out of houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What would they have had to have done - they had to be noisy or they had to be ill treating their wives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Yes it always - yes, and generally drink you know. I remember another time when I was quite small, a man taking his belt from round - these men used to wear belts round their waists then and - a
nd hitting this woman with this belt. I - I - I, you know, it used to scare me. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Can you remember anyone ever}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11228406\charrsid804585  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 making an effigy of someone and parading up and down outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. No. Don't remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, me mother used to say, try and do one kind action every day no matter who it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Were you ever told to curtsey or show respect in some way to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes, we were always taught to respect - people. NO matter how old they were - respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Show respect for an older person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It didn't matter who they were - just because they were older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 That's right yes. Go and carry their basket or do something for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Was there anyone you called Sir or Master or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes - when - the gentleman at church we saw we always used to say sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Which gentleman would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 these that lived down Aigburth Drive and Linnet Lane and - Livingstone Drive. We always used to Sir them when we were children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Why do you think that would have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 I - I don't know Mrs - it was just that we were told to do it and - yes. No, no, didn't think about it - it was right and we did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. No, I don't No. no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 In the district where you lived who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you mean like in the shops? Well some - and the shopkeepers you know would think they - they must be very rich, having a shop. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Anybody else you might have thought important in the community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, only people in the shops 'cos they must have a lot of money to have a shop. Y
es. With paying their bills. I suppose we thought money in -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
You thought they were important because - you probably felt they had a lot of money. Who would you think the shopkeepers friends would have been - who would they have gone around with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Only the shopkeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 The other shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Who would the clergymen have associated with do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 The clergymen? Well the - the people round the Park. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What kind of occupations would they have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
These big gentlemen? Well they were a bit - mostly merchants weren't they. Yes. Of import and - cotton - cotton - a lot of cotton merchants used to live around there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And the clergy would more likely to be friendly with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh I think so. I 
think so. Although - very kindly - used to come and visit the poor you know and very, very nice. But I think they would keep in with the - the bigger people you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What about teachers - who would their friends have been do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 There was no teachers lived in Lark Lane you see. But - I don't know really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 If there were any farmers about who would their friends have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Farmers? There's no farmers - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And employers - who would their friends have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 I don't know - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What sort of people would you say went to the church of England church that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Oh we went to the Christchurch Linnet Lane in those days-were all these big people the church used to be full I believe on Sunday morning. Yes, with all these bigger -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 With these moneyed people you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes, Aigburth Drive and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Were they the only sort of people going to that church or would there be other kinds
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh - we all went from Lark Lane - we all went but - these were the big ones you see. But all very very nice. Very nice men and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Were there any very, very poor people who went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes, there's some from Ark Lane - a street down Hesketh Street and some very poor - but they - they made themselve
s nice on a Sunday - toddle off to church on a Sunday night you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What sort of people would have gone to the chapel then? Does the chapel mean anything to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Nothing at all 'cos I don't know anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Can you remember any friction between Catholics and Protestants where you lived?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Oh yes - my mother used to say now don't you good - that, they're naughty children. Now we used to come home from school with a - from St Michaels - and the children from St Charles, that's on Aigbu
rth Road, and of course some children always out for quarrelling you know and - there was - just quarrelling I think really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What sort of things would go on - what did they say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh - I wouldn't really know but I know the - the - one of them said
 to me once, you won't go to heaven. You won't go to heaven. You're going to the wrong school. You should come to our school. Yes. You know and - things - and then suppose I - I am going to heaven, you know, how children will talk. And I suppose just one 
t
hing led to another and in some cases then children would go home and tell their parents. Well there was always the parents that was up in arms in no time and then that would cause trouble you know and - but - it was very, very slight - 'cos we used to pl
ay with the children that went into - it's very, very wrong Mrs Hoskinson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Can you remember any fights between adults on particular occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, no, no, there's no - everybody was very nice. Yes. Yes. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It wasn't quite in the area where there was the most trouble was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
No there wasn't really - no, there wasn't - they were all very nice people and - when the priest - there was plenty of priests in them days and they'd soon stop any little trouble you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Where you lived
 did all the people in the class you put yourself in - the middle class group, have the same standard of living or would you say that there were different groups and they all had different standards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well - no, no, I - what was important in my family might not interest other people in - in - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 So people were different - they did have different standards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes. Yes. 'Cos I can remember I used to say, oh I don't want to mix with them, I don't like their ideas and - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Can you describe any families that would be very different from yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes, there's always some girl thought they were far better. Oh yes. Than we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Why would they think that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
I don't know but - we're - we're better off than you - I remember them saying that and we've got this and you haven't got that and - oh yes, remember I'd gone home telling me mother so and so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What would she say to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Take no notice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You think money was the main thing do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes, and if you had lots of ha'pennies and pennies and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Made them feel important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes. And of course some - some of these families, they never thought of going to 
church you know and - and their mothers - I know two houses their mothers were always out, I don't know where they went to but - these two mothers were never in - they'd go off somewhere. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You've already said some families were thought of as rough and some as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh well the man that was a craftsman, well he would think himself far above the poor labourer. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Can you remember things being said do you mean to illustrate that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 But no - not said Mrs Hoskinson but I know it - you know - the way they acted they thought themselves above -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another and can you remember anybody who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes, that was a very - oh now that's what I call a real lady and he's a real gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Why do you think people were described like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Because I think they had respect and - you know - they weren't stuck up. Some people if they had a little thing they'd be
 very stuck up and - but me mother used to say well they're the real lady and gentleman because they're not - they've just got their own nice ways and - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes. If we saw a policeman turn the corner of our street we'd all run home - we'd think he was coming for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did your mother ever say to you I'll send for the policeman if you'r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11228406\charrsid804585 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585  - not a good girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes. Not - not to me but she did to my brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Were you frightened of the policeman or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
We shouldn't have been 'cos they were all lovely you know and - he's supposed to be the one you should look up to and - run to and help. But I think it was the uniform really that used to - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What did you think of him really - do you think he treated people well or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Oh yes, they were all very very good. He only used to have to get his truncheon out and - you know, show it to you - oh we were away. Won't do it again - on't do it again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 That was both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Both of them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Not the man that owned the house - only the collector that came for the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What sort of person was he - was he friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Very nice as long as he got the rent. He never had to wait, the rent was always there. My father - yes, the rent had to be put in this little box, I can see it - yes, I can see the little box now, yes. That was the rent man's money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Put away as soon as your father got his money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 That's right. That was always put away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh I think they must have done many a time Mrs - they must have done really becau
se all those little feet to cover for one thing you know and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Can you remember feeling this or hearing them talking about something to make you aware of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. No. They never did any of that sort of talking in front of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 They always kept it for when they were on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Yes. But they must have been a big struggle, even in after years my mother never - you know, we - but when I look back myself it must have been a big struggle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 But you were never really aware of it at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You never went hungry or cold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Never. Never hungry or cold. And always a lovely fire in the grate and - plenty of milk and plenty of sugar and all that, plenty of food. But I do know girls in them days that - can't have anything 
'cos of me father comes home and - we've got no bread and - oh I do remember, in - in this street I lived, I've nothing 'til my father comes home with the money. I do, and I used to think it was dreadful you know and I'd say to my mother can you give some
 - well you can have a piece of bread and butter, that's all I can give them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Children always feel so sorry don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 In fact they're very kind hearted creatures, children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 I think so Mrs Hoskinson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Can you remember your parents ever getting help from the guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 My father would never - never have accepted it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 When there was someone in the district who the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well - yes, people would -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did they ever make rough music - bang tin cans outside their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes, they - they did - they used to do all - and tie the handles of the door - do all sorts of - yes, and then used to - g
o - like this and - to torment them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 To make them feel they didn't want them there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1137955\charrsid804585 Yes. And they'd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585  thro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1137955\charrsid804585 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585  all sorts of things in their backyard. They'd throw tin cans and - oh yes, dirty clothes and - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What would these people have had to have done to make other people behave like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well I don't really know Mrs Hoskinson unless it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Would it be for sort of beating his wife or living immorally or drunkenness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11228406\charrsid804585 Drunken}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1137955\charrsid804585 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11228406\charrsid804585 ess}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585  more than anything. Drunken}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1137955\charrsid804585 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 ess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Making a nuisance of himself being drunk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 That's - yes, yes. Drunken}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1137955\charrsid804585 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 ess was most in the - I don't remember anybody beating their - not - well there was one man but it was generally drunkenness. That - that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 People do funny things under the influence of drink don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 They - they - they do, yes, it was mostly drunke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1137955\charrsid804585 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1137955\charrsid804585 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 ss I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 This is what people didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes. Oh they'd bang on the door and run away and - yes, knock on the knocker. Used to have a lot of k
nockers in them days - bang, bang, bang. Yes. But knock knock - I can always remember that. Yes. Yes. Yes. What - they'd break the window too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Would it be only children that did this or would it be adults?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No - adults. We - we wouldn't do it - not with grown up people. Yes. One house in particular I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 People tend to take the law into their own hands if they disapprove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh they did in those sort - yes - and they was unkind on them and I can -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And they got a bad name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Oh yes, pity help anybody that got a bad name and - and the same people, if anybody was poor they'd be - taking jugs of soup and doing any little kindness, see they - they look - you know, people that were poorly but they couldn't bear anybody tha
t was - drunk or - and doing nasty - beastly things they used to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And they showed it by doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did you start at school or were you given lessons at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. Went to school. Went straight to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 When you first started what time of the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
We had to be there nine o'clock and we got out at twelve o'clock and we went back again for half past one and then we got out again at four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did you start all day or did you just start in the mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 All day. All day, yes. And it was such a long time you know. Such a long day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You thought you'd never see home again?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Church of England. Church school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How did you get to school and how long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It took about quarter of an hour to get there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And you would have walked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes. No, just walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Who would have taken you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 My mother took us at the beginning and then another person would take us, you know, if my mother couldn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Older children you would get to know would take you too would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes. I know a big girl used to bring me back}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1137955\charrsid804585  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 again at four o'clock because my mother was so - the trams were running then and she was so afraid I was getting run over. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did you come home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What did you think of school - did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Disliked it
. I didn't like it, no, because there was teachers there and - they used to shout and - they might not have been shouting at me but to hear their voices raised I suppose I was frightened and I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You mean you didn't have anything like this at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Your parents were very quiet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Yes. And I couldn't - and then if - the teacher would come and if you did something naughty - spoke - just said something to the next child they'd give you such a smack on the face. Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 They were quite sort of easy handed were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes. And I - that frightened the life out of me. It didn't happen very often but to the other children being punished you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It upset you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes it did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What did you think about the teachers if they raised their voices and smacked children - were there some you liked more than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Oh yes, there was two teachers I used to love and I used to worry my mother to give me some sweeties to take to them. And a little bunch of flowers or somet
hing like that. I just loved - a Miss Marriatt and - and Miss Bessie Jones. I can remember those two teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And they were more gentle were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes, they were gentle and very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life - such as manners, tidiness, punctuality?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Oh - we - we had to be clean and we had to show our hands as soon - you know ; morning and afternoon. We all had to put our hands out for the teacher to see - that they'd been washed and had our hair done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 So they liked you to be neat and tidy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What about punctuality and ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes, if - if we were late we got a black mark. Yes. We didn't get smacked for that I don't think. Not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It went down against you on the register?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen - you mentioned they would get a smack across the head?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Would they ever used the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes, we - we could see the cane hanging up. W
hen that cane - I think that frightened me as much as anything. And he - and - she did used to give the children a smack with the cane - they'd put their little hands out - I used to be crying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What would they have been punished with the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Done something wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What sort of thing would warrant the cane? Being cheeky?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes, and if they - sometimes they'd smack another child in front or - talking - mostly talking I thing. Yes, talking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Were the girls punished - was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It was a mixed school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Were the girls punished with the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes, just - oh yes, we all got the cane. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did your parents show an interest in your school work, did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes.
 Yes, soon as we came home my mother used to say, now show me what you've been doing and what has the teacher been telling you about today and then my father when - when he did see us - it wasn't very often - he said, now - count and let me see how far yo
u've got. Very, very interested, yes. Now let me see you writing and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did they ever visit the school or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. No. I know my father couldn't have gone and me mother wouldn't have time. She went down, if she though
t one of her children had been punished for something that wasn't right - she'd take the baby with her and just go down - I remember once or twice her going down. 'Cos my brother that was killed in the first world war, they seemed to have - I shan't say s
pite, but they seemed to have it in for him and they blamed him for things he didn't do. And - she was very, very upset. Yes. She said, I don't believe you 'cos he never does that at home, I'm sure he wouldn't do it here. Yes, she did -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Well some - some didn't come - I'm not meaning it in a nasty way - my - my home was a very nice home and me mother looked after us but some children came and they were dirty, Mrs - very neglected,
 yes. And - you know, nasty little things about and some of them used to smell awful, I remember that. And I used to say to my mother, I had to sit by somebody and they smelt horrible. And she'd send a little note and say could they move me somewhere else
. It wasn't their fault in many a case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You are offended by it if you're careful and clean yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 That's right Mrs - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others? Would they have treated these chi
ldren who were neglected any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
No. I don't think - no, I think they - they were very nice to the children. The only children - the clever children they used to take more interest in. Yes, they did - yes, yes, they'd give them special - you
 know - we'd just have to sit looking at our other - I was never one of the clever ones but - they were very nice, I won't say anything wrong like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 They felt if somebody had a little extra there they would help them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And the clever ones - t
he girl very clever and she used to read a story on Friday afternoon and - you know, I used to think that was very nice. 'Cos she was clever and she could read nicely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 So they encouraged this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Were there any gangs or groups in the school as far as you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, no, no. No. No - do you mean like they go about now - oh - no. No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Were there any children who were left out of things for any reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You were fourteen and a half when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Left school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did you attend any part time education afterwards - any night school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes - yes, I did go to night school - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What did you do at that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Dressmaking. Yes, I went in to try and learn dressmaking. I went two - two winters. Only in the winter evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did you enjoy that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It was very nice - but I didn't get - didn't learn anything very much. No, because they were cutting out on papers and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1137955\charrsid804585 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 aging things and - it was - no. No, it didn't interest me at all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Would you rather have got on with the sewing part of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 I would have like that part but not this cutting out with the paper. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well - sometimes - I - I do feel I wish I'd have - you know - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What makes you feel that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Although I learnt more after I left school than - yes, yes, I used to listen to ni
ce people talking and - you know. After you - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes, I do Mrs Hoskinson, oh yes, I mean if I hadn't have gone to school I wouldn't have been able to talk on anything at all you kno
w and the teachers were very nice, they said that when you grow up you've got to - learn and then you'll be able to talk about things. Little things that come in your memory now - yes, and think that - she was a nice teacher, she taught us that. Little bi
ts of poetry sometimes. It stays in your mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 While you were at school did you have any part time job where you would earn some money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. Well I went - used to take milk out in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Every morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 I don't know about - I don't think I went every morning and I got ninepence if I went every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Ninepence a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Just for mornings. And I think I went about twenty houses. There was a dairy in the street that I lived in. And so I didn't have very far to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How long would it have taken you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Well I should think it would be about an hour. I don't know. Ninepence. I didn't - I don't think I stayed there very long. No. I think - getting up so early in the morning, having to go to school. That's the only time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How did you-get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Oh well you see we used to buy our milk at this dairy. I think - I suppose she said to me, would you like to come and take milk out? I suppose I was thinking of the money. I don't think my mother wanted it or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did you give the ninepence to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 I might have given her tuppence or threepence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 She allowed you to keep the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It's quite vague in your mind is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It is really - yes. I might have given - she might have given - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What was your first full time job - at fourteen and a half when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well I didn't do anything for a long time - I was at home with my mother helping her. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How long for would you say, roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Well I - I tell you what it was. When - I'd be about seventeen. This - this lady - she had a brother and they were going to a bit house in Scotland and - me mother's lady said, would I like to go with them and help them with the children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And my
 mother thought it was very, very nice you see, to go up to Scotland and help the nurse that they had to look after these four little children. And I went there. It was in - I think it'd be about August - and I think I was there about six weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Can you remember quite a lot about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Well I remembered going and - it was very nice. I remember the little children - I know it was to a place in Scotland called - Selkirk. Yes. And a great big house - a beautiful house, and it was called the Hayning.
 You know it was so big I've never seen anything so big in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It quite impressed you did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How many servants did they employ at the house - there was the nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well they took - well you see they took all their servants with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How many of the would there have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well - quite eight I should think. Quite eight. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 There would have been a cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh they took the cook and the - the kitchen maid. I had nothing to do with them you see but I kn
ew - I knew some of them but I didn't - yes. I was with this nurse. I'd never met her before but she was very nice. Yes, she was very nice with me, 'cos she knew I was strange and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What did you call her and what did she call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 She called me Else - she called me Elsie - my name. I think I called her nurse. Yes, I called her nurse. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Where did you sleep and eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 In this -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Was there a servants' hall or anywhere else where you could sit when you weren't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh th
ere was a lovely big servants' hall. Very nice. And I used to be able to go out with the other - these other girls and we used to go lovely walks and they were very kind to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You had plenty of company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes. But I wanted to get home to me mothe
r. I thought the train was never going to stop. Oh I thought it was never going to stop. I can show you a picture of the house after. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You would eat in the servants' hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And sit in your own room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, I - only at night ti
me I went down there - just for company really. And - but - I had with a - this nurse and the children in a very nice room, 'course they called it the nursery and had it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You would have had your meals there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 With the nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did the mistress supervise all the housework personally or pass orders through the senior servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well I think they all knew their work. I don't think the - the lady herself was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It was well organised?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well organised, oh yes. The
y were very - they stayed practically - they were all - died - some of them were in that big house in Mossley hill you know, I told you about Well some of them - and see when they left there they went to a big house in Heswall called the Rosscott - they w
ent there - and they were there when they asked my mother could I go to this - one of her brothers you see to - with them - they thought it would be a nice change for me. Yes. And that's when I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did you feel at ease with the servants and the members of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh - they were all very nice. Every one - I couldn't find - say anything wrong about - they were all very kind and nice. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How did the servants and the members of the family address each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well I know they used to say ma'am - and sir. Yes. I'd call the gentleman sir too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 And call each other by their Christian names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
You never hear that Mrs - when we were young and we went to see our doctor we always used to say sir to him. Well I noticed to your husband - none of them ever said it at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Times have changed haven't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes. Respect's gone altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 It's a shame really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did you feel that any of them were interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 They were Mrs Hoskinson, 'cos knowing my mother you see they were all very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Very interested in you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 
Very nice - even the ladies and gentlemen of the family, they used to come and ask me, have you heard from your mother? How is she? Yes, they were all very very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did the mistress give any moral guidance to her servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes - they were real Christian people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Were they allowed any time to do just what they liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well Mrs - she was - they were old fashioned and I'd just grown up you see t
hat - it was all maids - the waitress, she was Miss Stewart, she was real Scotch, she was lovely, she was there with my mother and - in - and she was just lovely. And the cook - she'd been there many, many years. She died there. They all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 They must have been very good to their servants for them to have stayed like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 When could they go out of the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well they could go when practically they'd like you know but they never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 What sort of time off would they have had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well - I think - my mother when she was young, she had one day every three months in those days that - yes, but she had nowhere to go.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 So she wasn't unhappy about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No. Oh no. And the others, you see, were - there parents and rela
tions lived far away. I think they'd just pop into town and they'd come back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Just for a quick sort of trip round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes. You see, life was so different in them days. They didn't want to go far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Did she mind what they did when they went out of the house or when they returned - would there be a time when they had to be in by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 I suppose ten o'clock was the time but I don't think any of them stayed out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 They weren't that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 They'd probably be in before you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Would she have known what they were going to do - would she have asked them where they were going when they went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Well, she might have done - she was very interested in them all - she trusted them all and they all loved her and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 A quite happy relationship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes. All the way through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 You said you missed your mother - did you feel very homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh - I thought when I - you haven't been here one week yes - I remember saying that, I haven't been here one 
week yet and I've got another five weeks. Oh - oh but I always remembered going from - I suppose it would be Exchange Station and I thought the train was never going to stop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Were you lonely or did you have enough companionship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, I couldn't s
ay I was lonely because they were all - the - there were some young people there. And they were all - used to go and say - we're going so and so, there's a concert on, would you like to come with us? Of course I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Made you feel pat of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Was there anything you particularly liked or disliked about that situation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, I - I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No strong dislikes or likes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 No, it was very, very nice.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 How did the housework go - the maids and this sort of thing would get on with it would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Oh yes. It was a great big place. They always seemed to be working to me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Keeping it going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3152901 EW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 Yes, yes. There's such a lot - 'cos they had - such a lot of visitors - entertaining you know - such a big place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6829769 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5202159\charrsid804585 There was a lot to do?
